[South Ossetia, formerly the South Ossetian Autonomous Oblast within
the former Georgian Soviet Socialist Republic, is a disputed region
which declared independence from Georgia in 1990, calling themselves
the "Republic of South Ossetia." Following several political and
military events, the Ossetian separatists and Russian troops gained
de-facto control of the territory since 2008. See map at
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:South_Ossetia_overview_map.png.

Official information from a competent authority is requested. -
